Desert Hawk Gold Corp. Key Developments

Desert Hawk Gold Corp. Announces Management Changes
Apr 7 17
On April 3, 2017, John May and Michael Kurtanjek each resigned from their positions as directors of Desert Hawk Gold Corp. On April 6, 2017, the Board of Directors of the company reduced the number of authorized directors to three and appointed John P. Ryan as a director of the company to fill the vacancy left by Mr. May's resignation as a director. On April 6, 2017, the Board of Directors of the company appointed Rick Havenstrite as Chief Executive Officer and Principal Executive Officer of the company to replace Howard Crosby. Mr. Havenstrite has served as the company's President since April 2009. Since May 1999 he has been the co-owner and president of Overhead Door Company of Sierra/Nevada Inc.


Desert Hawk Gold Corp. announced delayed annual 10-K filing
Apr 3 17
On 04/03/2017, Desert Hawk Gold Corp. announced that they will be unable to file their next 10-K by the deadline required by the SEC.


Desert Hawk Gold Corp. Announces Executive Changes
Mar 14 17
On March 13, 2017, John Ryan resigned from his position as Chief Financial Officer and Principal Financial and Accounting Officer of Desert Hawk Gold Corp. Marianne Havenstrite, the company's Treasurer, will assume the role of Principal Financial and Accounting Officer.


